LEGIONELLOSIS - USA (MARYLAND)
******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Legionellosis - USA (Maryland) 981010101415
Date: Thu, 8 Jul 1999 08:21:41 -0400
From: Murphy, James H. <JAMES.H.MURPHY@cpmx.saic.com>

Radio reports in the Baltimore area on 8 July 1999 provided information
that the Harford Memorial Hospital has reported an apparent outbreak of
Legionnaires' disease in Harford County, Maryland. The hospital has cared
for four (4) patients with Legionnaires'-like symptoms, experiencing two
(2) fatalities thus far. Hospital officials are stating that they suspect
the disease originated at the hospital, but that has yet to be determined.
Samples from the hospital's air and water systems are being [analyzed; the
results [are not yet available. The hospital has contacted all persons
who have been patients at the hospital in the last two (2) weeks, providing
them the signs and symptoms and instructions for contacting the hospital if
they develop such.
--
J. Howard Murphy, CEM
Harford County resident
e-mail: JAMES.H.MURPHY@cpmx.saic.com
